metaData.descriptionCS: For Digit Span Forward, the child repeats numbers in the same order as read aloud by the examiner. For Digit Span Backward, the child repeats numbers in the reverse order of that presented aloud by the examiner.

trials.topInstructionsHTML:
Say, I’m going to say some numbers. Listen carefully, I can only say them one time. When I stop, you say them back to me in the same order. Just say what I say.

Read each Digit Span trial verbatim at the rate of one digit per second, dropping your voice inflection slightly on the last digit in the sequence. Pause to allow the child to respond.

2 – 9
trials.title: Forward Item 1 Trial 1

consecutiveZerosDiscontinueRule.description: Discontinue after score of 0 on qualifying item or score of 0 on both trials of an item.

trials.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, That’s not quite right. I said 9 – 4, so to say them backward, you should say 4 – 9.
trials.topInstructionsHTML:
Say, Now I’m going to say some more numbers, but this time when I stop, you say the numbers backward.

If I say 9 – 4, what would you say?
trials.title: Backward Sample Item Trial 1

trials.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response:

Say, That’s right. Let’s try some more.
trials.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, That’s not quite right. I said 5 – 6, so to say them backward, you should say 6 – 5. Let’s try some more.
trials.topInstructionsHTML: Say, Let’s try another one. Remember to say them backward: 5 – 6.
trials.title: Backward Sample Item Trial 2

consecutiveZerosDiscontinueRule.description: Discontinue after score of 0 on qualifying item or score of 0 on both trials of an item.

questions.title: Sequencing Qualifying Item
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Proceed according to the instructions that follow.
questions.topInstructionsHTML:
Say, Count to five out loud so I can hear you.

If it appears that the child does not understand, say, Count, like this, 1...2... (pause between each number). Now you try. Allow the child to respond.

trials.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, That’s not quite right. I said 3 – 1. To say them in order, starting with the smallest number, you should say 1 – 3.
trials.topInstructionsHTML:
Say, Now I’m going to say some more numbers, but this time when I stop, you say the numbers in order, starting with the smallest number.

If I say 3 – 1, what would you say?
trials.title: Sequencing Sample Item A Trial 1

trials.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, That’s not quite right. I said 8 – 6. To say them in order, starting with the smallest number, you should say 6 – 8.
trials.title: Sequencing Sample Item A Trial 2

trials.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, That’s not quite right. I said 5 – 2 – 4. To say them in order, starting with the smallest number, you should say 2 – 4 – 5.
trials.title: Sequencing Sample Item B Trial 1

trials.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response:

Say, That’s right. Let’s try some more.
trials.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect response:

Say, That’s not quite right. I said 4 – 3 – 3. To say them in order, starting with the smallest number, you should say 3 – 3 – 4. You may have to say the same number more than one time. Let’s try some more.
trials.title: Sequencing Sample Item B Trial 2

consecutiveZerosDiscontinueRule.description: Discontinue after score of 0 on qualifying item or score of 0 on both trials of an item.
